WEBVTT

00:02.802 --> 00:05.472
[***]

00:05.505 --> 00:07.574
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>When you first become</i>
<i>a teenager,</i>

00:07.607 --> 00:10.076
<i>you think it's cool</i>
<i>to just be a teenager.</i>

00:10.110 --> 00:12.612
<i>Then you find out</i>
<i>no matter how cool you act,</i>

00:12.645 --> 00:16.416
<i>if you don't look cool, you</i>
<i>might as well be 5 years old.</i>

00:16.449 --> 00:19.152
<i>And the coolest thing</i>
<i>you could have when I was 13</i>

00:19.185 --> 00:20.286
<i>was a leather jacket.</i>

00:20.320 --> 00:22.222
<i>He might not have a daddy,</i>

00:22.255 --> 00:24.491
<i>but he's got a leather jacket.</i>

00:27.193 --> 00:29.262
Keisha, you got
a leather jacket too?

00:29.295 --> 00:31.564
My mom just got it
off layaway for me.

00:31.598 --> 00:33.166
I was thinking
about getting one.

00:33.199 --> 00:35.402
You are? Why?

00:35.435 --> 00:38.204
Look at me.
I'm skinny and I'm short.

00:38.238 --> 00:40.106
I'm not gonna
become cool overnight.

00:40.140 --> 00:41.841
You don't look
that bad, though.

00:41.875 --> 00:44.377
Yeah, but I need something.

00:44.411 --> 00:46.212
Think a leather jacket
would help?

00:46.246 --> 00:47.781
I guess.

00:47.814 --> 00:50.417
<i>All I was thinking is that</i>
<i>the right leather jacket</i>

00:50.450 --> 00:54.554
<i>would have turned me</i>
<i>from this guy...into this guy.</i>

00:54.587 --> 00:57.157
Chris.
That leather jacket is cool.

00:57.190 --> 00:58.458
Let's hang out.

00:58.491 --> 01:01.127
As soon as
I'm finished posing.

01:06.566 --> 01:08.768
<i>I knew where to get</i>
<i>a leather jacket.</i>

01:08.802 --> 01:11.771
<i>Now all I needed was money.</i>

01:11.805 --> 01:14.107
[***]

01:19.546 --> 01:22.215
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

01:47.507 --> 01:50.677
A leather jacket? What do you
need a leather jacket for?

01:50.710 --> 01:52.645
Keisha said it was cool.

01:52.679 --> 01:54.781
Think a leather jacket's
gonna make you cool?

01:54.814 --> 01:57.417
<i>It made these guys</i>
<i>gazillionaires.</i>

01:57.450 --> 02:01.654
It could. The only thing is,
I don't have $50.

02:01.688 --> 02:03.356
Just save up your allowance.

02:03.390 --> 02:05.358
My what?
Your allowance.

02:05.392 --> 02:07.794
It's money that your parents
give you every week.

02:07.827 --> 02:09.362
<i>I'd heard about allowances,</i>

02:09.396 --> 02:11.197
<i>but I didn't know</i>
<i>they actually existed.</i>

02:11.231 --> 02:14.234
<i>I thought it was just something</i>
<i>that happened on TV.</i>

02:14.267 --> 02:16.936
Here you go, son.
A thousand dollars.

02:16.970 --> 02:17.937
Thank you, father.

02:17.971 --> 02:20.373
[CHUCKLING]

02:20.407 --> 02:22.642
<i>Since my father</i>
<i>was always working,</i>

02:22.676 --> 02:24.511
<i>he always seemed</i>
<i>kind of grumpy.</i>

02:24.544 --> 02:26.579
<i>It seemed like there was</i>
<i>never a good time</i>

02:26.613 --> 02:28.314
<i>to ask my father for money.</i>

02:28.348 --> 02:29.983
Daddy, can I have $15
to go on a field trip

02:30.016 --> 02:32.652
to the Statue of Liberty?
Okay.

02:32.686 --> 02:34.921
Hey, Dad, can I have $5
to go to the show?

02:34.954 --> 02:36.723
Okay.

02:36.756 --> 02:38.925
Baby, can I get $25
to go shopping?

02:38.958 --> 02:40.760
Okay.

02:40.794 --> 02:43.396
<i>It looks like this might be</i>
<i>a good time after all.</i>

02:43.430 --> 02:46.466
Hey, Dad?
Can I get a leather jacket?

02:46.499 --> 02:49.402
A leather jacket? You got
some leather-jacket money?

02:49.436 --> 02:51.338
What do you need
a leather jacket for?

02:51.371 --> 02:52.772
What's wrong
with Drew's old coat?

02:52.806 --> 02:54.908
<i>Instead of Drew wearing</i>
<i>my old clothes,</i>

02:54.941 --> 02:56.643
<i>I wore his old clothes.</i>

02:56.676 --> 02:58.978
<i>I think I was the first kid</i>
<i>to get hand-me-ups.</i>

02:59.012 --> 03:01.481
It's too small,
it's out of style

03:01.514 --> 03:03.316
and it's just not cool.

03:03.350 --> 03:04.818
It ain't supposed to be cool.

03:04.851 --> 03:06.486
It's supposed to be warm.

03:06.519 --> 03:07.854
Being warm is cool.

03:07.887 --> 03:10.623
I'm not asking you to buy it.
I'll save up.

03:10.657 --> 03:11.825
Save up what?

03:11.858 --> 03:16.563
I was hoping you can give me
an allowance.

03:16.596 --> 03:19.366
<i>I know it sounded like</i>
<i>an innocent enough question,</i>

03:19.399 --> 03:20.567
<i>but here's what he heard.</i>

03:20.600 --> 03:22.435
Since you work
like a slave all day

03:22.469 --> 03:26.473
and don't have time to enjoy
your money, can I have it?

03:28.608 --> 03:31.311
I'm not giving you money
for doing nothing.

03:31.344 --> 03:32.612
An allowance?

03:32.645 --> 03:35.048
I'll allow you
to sleep here at night.

03:35.081 --> 03:37.317
I'll allow you
to eat them potatoes.

03:37.350 --> 03:38.718
I'll allow you to use my lights.

03:38.752 --> 03:41.321
I'll allow you
to drink my Kool-Aid.

03:41.354 --> 03:43.623
I'll allow you to nibble
on them green beans.

03:43.656 --> 03:45.658
I'll allow you
to look at that TV.

03:45.692 --> 03:48.061
I'll allow you
to run up my gas bill.

03:48.094 --> 03:49.863
I'll allow you
to walk up my stairs.

03:49.896 --> 03:53.600
I'll allow you to ask me
these ridiculous-ass questions.

03:53.633 --> 03:55.735
Why should I give you
an allowance

03:55.769 --> 03:58.738
when I already paid for
everything you do?

03:58.772 --> 04:02.742
Who you know that gets
an allowance? Huh?

04:02.776 --> 04:04.644
I'm finished.

04:04.678 --> 04:07.847
I was talking to Greg.
He said that he gets $5 a week.

04:07.881 --> 04:10.383
Sounds like Greg's
doing better than me.

04:10.417 --> 04:12.452
Ask him for an allowance.

04:12.485 --> 04:14.454
You want to buy a leather coat,

04:14.487 --> 04:16.823
you need to get
a leather-coat job.

04:16.856 --> 04:19.726
<i>While things might have been</i>
<i>tight with my father,</i>

04:19.759 --> 04:21.728
<i>my mother was getting loose.</i>

04:21.761 --> 04:25.732
<i>She was always happy when</i>
<i>she had the house to herself.</i>

04:25.765 --> 04:28.001
<i>She caught up on her reading.</i>

04:28.034 --> 04:30.804
<i>She talked on the phone.</i>

04:30.837 --> 04:34.040
<i>She ate expensive candy</i>
<i>she hid from us.</i>

04:34.074 --> 04:36.976
<i>But there was one thing</i>
<i>that she never counted on</i>

04:37.010 --> 04:39.079
<i>to mess up her day.</i>

04:40.880 --> 04:42.716
Coming...

04:44.617 --> 04:46.019
What are y'all doing here?

04:46.052 --> 04:48.388
Something went wrong
at our school.

04:48.421 --> 04:50.490
Something about the paint.

04:53.093 --> 04:56.529
<i>Before vending machines were</i>
<i>put into schools,</i>

04:56.563 --> 04:59.933
<i>hungry kids often snacked</i>
<i>on lead paint chips.</i>

04:59.966 --> 05:01.768
Mm.

05:01.801 --> 05:04.838
This is good!

05:04.871 --> 05:07.607
<i>If we had ladders,</i>
<i>he'd have ate the asbestos.</i>

05:07.640 --> 05:09.642
I want one!
Me too! Me too! Me too!

05:09.676 --> 05:12.846
Come on, me too!
Hey, give me some!

05:12.879 --> 05:15.081
So we can go back
after they finish

05:15.115 --> 05:16.549
repainting our classrooms.

05:16.583 --> 05:18.418
All right, well,
stay out of my way,

05:18.451 --> 05:19.552
'cause I'm cleaning up.

05:19.586 --> 05:20.920
What are we gonna do all day?

05:20.954 --> 05:22.856
I don't know. Go play.

05:24.791 --> 05:29.696
But you all better not mess up
my house till after 4:30!

05:29.729 --> 05:34.034
I mean, asbestos kills.
A little paint ain't gonna hurt.

05:34.067 --> 05:37.904
<i>After a day out of school, my</i>
<i>mother wasn't having any fun.</i>

05:37.937 --> 05:40.173
<i>And neither were</i>
<i>Tonya and Drew.</i>

05:40.206 --> 05:42.575
What are you doing?
Nothing.

05:42.609 --> 05:44.144
<i>When broke kids get bored,</i>

05:44.177 --> 05:47.047
<i>they play one of the cheapest</i>
<i>games ever invented:</i>

05:47.080 --> 05:48.481
<i>"I Dare You."</i>

05:48.515 --> 05:49.816
I dare you

05:49.849 --> 05:53.687
to put these ice cubes
under your armpit.

05:53.720 --> 05:56.923
For how long?
One minute.

05:56.956 --> 05:58.425
Okay.

05:59.626 --> 06:02.629
Whoo! Ah!
One...

06:02.662 --> 06:05.732
two...
Count normal, Tonya.

06:05.765 --> 06:08.568
Three...
What is wrong with you?

06:08.601 --> 06:11.504
I dared him to put
ice cubes under his arms.

06:11.538 --> 06:14.574
Take the ice cubes
from under your arm.

06:14.607 --> 06:16.609
Not...in the glass.

06:16.643 --> 06:18.645
Boy, people gotta drink
from that.

06:18.678 --> 06:21.481
Okay, I dare you to drink it.

06:21.514 --> 06:23.983
You better not. That's nasty.
I'm not.

06:24.017 --> 06:26.052
Know what, since y'all
want to dare so bad,

06:26.086 --> 06:29.923
dare each other to sit down and
act like y'all got some sense.

06:29.956 --> 06:33.626
How about that? I'll be glad
when y'all go back to school.

06:33.660 --> 06:35.562
You are driving me
up the wall.

06:35.595 --> 06:36.963
Two walls.

06:36.996 --> 06:40.567
Now you have to do something.
That's nasty.

06:40.600 --> 06:42.702
<i>Meanwhile, I felt like</i>
<i>the only guy on earth</i>

06:42.736 --> 06:44.871
<i>without a leather jacket.</i>
You got a leather jacket?

06:44.904 --> 06:48.174
Cool, huh? My dad got it for me
at the army surplus store.

06:48.208 --> 06:49.676
Hey, weren't you the one

06:49.709 --> 06:51.511
who said leather
didn't make you cool?

06:51.544 --> 06:53.580
Yeah, but I was wrong.

06:53.613 --> 06:55.982
So, what did your dad say
about an allowance?

06:56.016 --> 06:59.185
He said no...
for about two hours.

06:59.219 --> 07:01.588
Hi, Greg. Nice jacket.

07:01.621 --> 07:04.057
Wait, she's talking to you?

07:04.090 --> 07:05.892
Cool, huh?

07:05.925 --> 07:08.795
I gotta get me
a leather jacket.

07:08.828 --> 07:10.530
<i>Finding a job when you're 13</i>

07:10.563 --> 07:12.198
<i>is not the easiest thing to do.</i>

07:12.232 --> 07:13.967
<i>I applied for easy jobs...</i>

07:14.000 --> 07:16.936
Now, why would I pay you
to put groceries in a bag

07:16.970 --> 07:19.973
when I can put them in a bag
my damn self?

07:20.006 --> 07:24.077
<i>I applied for hard jobs...</i>
Security guard, huh?

07:24.110 --> 07:25.912
You ever been shot?

07:25.945 --> 07:28.815
<i>I even applied for jobs I</i>
<i>didn't know I was applying for.</i>

07:28.848 --> 07:31.551
You any good with matches?

07:31.584 --> 07:33.219
There's a new barber
down the block.

07:33.253 --> 07:36.089
He needs to be taught a lesson.

07:36.122 --> 07:37.557
[TONYA GIGGLES]

07:37.590 --> 07:39.893
I dare you
to slide down these stairs

07:39.926 --> 07:43.229
on your back.
Give me the towel.

07:43.263 --> 07:46.199
<i>Only place more dangerous</i>
<i>than the streets of Brooklyn</i>

07:46.232 --> 07:47.701
<i>were the hallways of Brooklyn.</i>

07:47.734 --> 07:49.769
[THUDDING]
[DREW GROANING]

07:49.803 --> 07:51.771
<i>After running out of options,</i>

07:51.805 --> 07:53.573
<i>I could only think</i>
<i>of one person</i>

07:53.606 --> 07:55.241
<i>that could help me find work.</i>

07:55.275 --> 07:56.843
Hey.

07:56.876 --> 07:59.779
Dad, can you help me
get a job?

07:59.813 --> 08:02.916
What?
I want to get a leather jacket.

08:02.949 --> 08:06.586
I've been trying to get a job,
but it's not working out so far.

08:06.619 --> 08:09.956
You want it that bad, huh?
Yeah.

08:09.989 --> 08:12.625
Want to come to work with me?
For real?

08:12.659 --> 08:14.561
Yeah. Tomorrow's Saturday.

08:14.594 --> 08:15.995
You can come do deliveries
with me.

08:16.029 --> 08:19.833
I'll be back in a few hours.
Now, be downstairs at 3:30.

08:19.866 --> 08:22.869
Not 3:31.
Don't worry. I'll be down early.

08:22.902 --> 08:24.104
No such thing as early.

08:24.137 --> 08:25.972
You're either on time
or you're late.

08:26.006 --> 08:28.041
<i>I was committed to getting</i>
<i>that jacket.</i>

08:28.074 --> 08:31.144
<i>Nothing was going to stop me.</i>
<i>Nothing except a nap.</i>

08:31.177 --> 08:33.780
[***]

08:44.691 --> 08:46.026
[HORN HONKING]

08:46.059 --> 08:48.128
[SNORING]

08:50.063 --> 08:51.931
[ENGINE REVVING]

08:53.400 --> 08:57.804
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

09:03.176 --> 09:06.112
ANNOUNCER [ON TV]:
<i>He pulls up and shoots</i>
<i>the 12-footer.</i>

09:06.146 --> 09:09.315
<i>Vandross got the rebound.</i>
<i>He lays it up and in.</i>

09:09.349 --> 09:12.752
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>I thought my father would be</i>
<i>mad that I missed work.</i>

09:12.786 --> 09:14.254
<i>Instead of getting</i>
<i>a leather jacket,</i>

09:14.287 --> 09:16.723
<i>I thought I was</i>
<i>gonna get a leather belt.</i>

09:16.756 --> 09:18.091
What happened this morning?

09:18.124 --> 09:21.361
I overslept.
How come you didn't come get me?

09:21.394 --> 09:23.263
You the one want the job.

09:23.296 --> 09:24.931
Job ain't gonna wait for you.

09:27.801 --> 09:29.869
[***]

09:29.903 --> 09:32.305
<i>In the game of dare,</i>
<i>there are no rules,</i>

09:32.339 --> 09:35.208
<i>there are no regulations</i>
<i>and the game doesn't end</i>

09:35.241 --> 09:37.077
<i>till somebody's dead.</i>

09:52.125 --> 09:54.794
I dare you.

09:54.828 --> 09:57.697
What you gonna give me?

09:57.731 --> 09:59.065
Two dollars.

10:01.301 --> 10:04.237
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

10:04.270 --> 10:07.140
Drink it. Hurry up.

10:07.173 --> 10:08.408
Hurry up, Tonya.

10:08.441 --> 10:10.010
More.

10:10.043 --> 10:12.946
Drink it. Whoa!

10:12.979 --> 10:15.415
[GROANING]

10:17.283 --> 10:19.753
Heh-heh, cool.

10:23.790 --> 10:26.159
How was it?

10:26.192 --> 10:28.028
Give me my $2.

10:28.061 --> 10:29.696
[ALARM BUZZES]

10:29.729 --> 10:31.164
<i>The next morning,</i>
<i>I was up earlier</i>

10:31.197 --> 10:33.199
<i>than a Marine</i>
<i>with a paper route.</i>

10:33.233 --> 10:34.934
Coffee?

10:34.968 --> 10:37.771
[MACHINERY WHIRRING, SQUEALING]

10:37.804 --> 10:40.006
<i>Working with my father</i>
<i>was mind-blowing.</i>

10:40.040 --> 10:41.975
<i>I couldn't believe</i>
<i>how big it was,</i>

10:42.008 --> 10:45.245
<i>how loud it was,</i>
<i>how fast everything was going.</i>

10:45.278 --> 10:47.981
<i>I felt like an Amish kid</i>
<i>in Vegas.</i>

10:48.014 --> 10:49.449
Come on.

10:50.850 --> 10:53.119
JULIUS: What's up, George?
Hey, Herc.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.822
What's up?
Hey!

10:55.855 --> 10:58.825
Who's this?
That's my son, Chris.

10:58.858 --> 11:01.494
Who's Herc?
Herc, like Hercules.

11:01.528 --> 11:03.129
That's a strong man.

11:03.163 --> 11:05.265
<i>The only other names</i>
<i>I knew my father by</i>

11:05.298 --> 11:07.267
<i>were the words</i>
<i>my mother called him,</i>

11:07.300 --> 11:09.869
<i>and they didn't have nothing</i>
<i>to do with being strong.</i>

11:09.903 --> 11:12.906
So, little Herc,
you funny like your old man?

11:12.939 --> 11:14.741
My father's funny?

11:14.774 --> 11:16.376
Nah, he ain't that funny.

11:16.409 --> 11:17.911
[BOTH LAUGHING]

11:17.944 --> 11:19.412
Funnier than you two corny...

11:19.446 --> 11:21.014
[HORN HONKS]
[MEN EXCLAIM]

11:21.047 --> 11:23.283
<i>My father never cursed</i>
<i>at home,</i>

11:23.316 --> 11:25.218
<i>so hearing him curse</i>
<i>at the job</i>

11:25.251 --> 11:27.187
<i>made me feel like</i>
<i>I was in a secret club.</i>

11:27.220 --> 11:30.056
Get to work before
I bring your mama back in here.

11:30.090 --> 11:31.191
Oh, no. No mamas.

11:31.224 --> 11:34.060
Yeah, okay, whatever you say.
See you, Little Herc.

11:34.094 --> 11:36.062
Tell your mama
to come back here too, man.

11:36.096 --> 11:40.333
[HORN HONKING]
[ALL LAUGHING]

11:40.367 --> 11:41.835
Hey, let's get to work.

11:41.868 --> 11:43.303
<i>I haven't heard cursing</i>
<i>like that</i>

11:43.336 --> 11:46.806
<i>since my father stepped</i>
<i>on my mother's bunion.</i>

11:46.840 --> 11:48.742
[TONYA GROANS]

11:51.211 --> 11:54.781
[TONYA GROANING, CRYING]

11:54.814 --> 11:56.950
<i>At home, the dare game</i>
<i>was over,</i>

11:56.983 --> 11:59.085
<i>but the trouble</i>
<i>was just starting.</i>

11:59.119 --> 12:00.887
[TOILET FLUSHES]

12:00.920 --> 12:03.023
[GROANING SOFTLY]

12:06.092 --> 12:09.295
What's wrong, baby? I heard you
all the way from my room.

12:09.329 --> 12:11.798
My stomach hurts really bad.

12:11.831 --> 12:13.233
Let me feel.

12:13.266 --> 12:16.236
Oh, no. You're burning up.
Let me feel your tummy.

12:16.269 --> 12:17.804
[SQUEALS, CRYING]

12:17.837 --> 12:20.206
Okay, baby, I'm gonna take you
to the emergency room.

12:20.240 --> 12:22.342
I'm gonna get your coat.
Drew, get up!

12:22.375 --> 12:24.577
<i>Going to the doctor</i>
<i>was serious business,</i>

12:24.611 --> 12:27.380
<i>because usually, if something</i>
<i>was wrong with one of us,</i>

12:27.414 --> 12:31.484
<i>my parents thought they could</i>
<i>fix it with Robitussin.</i>

12:31.518 --> 12:34.387
Ow! I burned my finger!

12:34.421 --> 12:36.956
Oh, let me see, boy, let me see.

12:36.990 --> 12:39.826
Oh, take some Robitussin.

12:39.859 --> 12:41.528
Looks like a tooth
broke off.

12:41.561 --> 12:44.431
Mm. I'll go get the Robitussin.

12:44.464 --> 12:45.965
(BANGING ON DOOR)

12:45.999 --> 12:48.134
ROCHELLE: What?
Chris just got hit by a car.

12:48.168 --> 12:52.405
Oh, my God,
I'll go get the Robitussin.

12:52.439 --> 12:54.841
[GROANING]

12:54.874 --> 12:57.477
I'm not telling her.
You're the one who drank it.

12:57.510 --> 13:01.314
You dared me!
Shh. Be quiet.

13:01.348 --> 13:03.950
Okay, come on. Let's go.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.292
<i>It was cold outside.</i>

13:12.325 --> 13:14.994
<i>I was tired,</i>
<i>and those papers were heavy.</i>

13:15.028 --> 13:16.296
<i>I was starting to wonder</i>

13:16.329 --> 13:18.932
<i>if that leather jacket</i>
<i>was worth it.</i>

13:18.965 --> 13:21.267
Hey, Chris.
What time you getting off?

13:21.301 --> 13:24.371
Never.
I gotta pay off this jacket.

13:30.310 --> 13:31.411
Okay, that's it.

13:31.444 --> 13:33.313
Good. Now can we have a break?

13:33.346 --> 13:36.216
We don't get a break
for another three hours.

13:36.249 --> 13:38.551
Come on.

13:38.585 --> 13:40.220
[SIRENS BLARING]

13:40.253 --> 13:43.223
<i>If you watch TV, you know</i>
<i>that an emergency room</i>

13:43.256 --> 13:47.327
<i>is one of the most exciting</i>
<i>places you can be.</i>

13:47.360 --> 13:49.229
<i>Wrong.</i>

13:49.262 --> 13:51.164
Yeah, Charlie and Karen,
They broke up.

13:51.197 --> 13:53.299
No!
Well, he went back to New York.

13:53.333 --> 13:56.302
Excuse me, nurse. My baby's
stomach is killing her.

13:56.336 --> 13:58.571
<i>The thing about people who work</i>
<i>in emergency rooms</i>

13:58.605 --> 14:01.641
<i>is they're not the ones</i>
<i>with the emergency, you are.</i>

14:01.675 --> 14:05.412
Really? Oh, but did you see
Tracy with her new man?

14:05.445 --> 14:08.348
But do you see me standing here
with a sick child?

14:08.381 --> 14:10.917
Do you see me here
talking to somebody?

14:10.950 --> 14:13.053
Quit hollerin' at people!
I don't need this.

14:13.086 --> 14:15.288
My man has three jobs!

14:16.656 --> 14:19.092
[***]

14:20.727 --> 14:22.562
<i>Being at work with my father</i>

14:22.595 --> 14:26.299
<i>was one of the coolest things</i>
<i>I ever did. We broke laws...</i>

14:26.332 --> 14:28.201
Oh! Hey, we can make it!
That's red!

14:28.234 --> 14:31.037
Hold on, man. Here we go. Whoa!

14:31.071 --> 14:32.372
Let's go! Let's go!
Aah!

14:34.107 --> 14:36.343
Whoo!
Ha-ha-ha!

14:36.376 --> 14:37.444
Yeah!
Yeah!

14:37.477 --> 14:38.945
<i>...cursed people out.</i>

14:38.978 --> 14:40.714
[HORN HONKING]

14:40.747 --> 14:44.084
Hurry up! Let's go!
Get out of the way!

14:45.585 --> 14:46.586
[HORN BLARING]

14:46.619 --> 14:48.488
Kiss my ass! That's right!

14:48.521 --> 14:51.224
You too! That's right!

14:51.257 --> 14:54.194
<i>That was one of the most</i>
<i>exciting nights of my life.</i>

14:54.227 --> 14:56.563
<i>We delivered papers</i>
<i>in Brooklyn.</i>

14:56.596 --> 15:00.300
<i>We delivered papers in Queens,</i>
<i>Little Italy, Chinatown,</i>

15:00.333 --> 15:02.969
<i>Spanish Harlem,</i>
<i>Puerto Rican Harlem,</i>

15:03.003 --> 15:04.671
<i>the Bronx, Greenwich Village.</i>

15:04.704 --> 15:08.141
<i>We delivered papers to people</i>
<i>I didn't even know could read.</i>

15:08.174 --> 15:12.379
<i>And after delivering more than</i>
<i>15 tons' worth of newspapers,</i>

15:12.412 --> 15:16.349
<i>all I could think was,</i>
<i>"Where the hell is the sun?"</i>

15:20.420 --> 15:23.356
Um, number 36, the doctor
will see you now.

15:23.390 --> 15:26.393
Oh, no, no, no! Come on!
This is ridiculous!

15:26.426 --> 15:29.229
Who's gonna help my baby?
That man's been shot.

15:29.262 --> 15:31.631
Just because she's not shot
doesn't mean she isn't hurt.

15:31.664 --> 15:33.266
If this wasn't an emergency,

15:33.299 --> 15:35.368
we wouldn't have come
to the emergency room.

15:35.402 --> 15:37.737
Look, if she doesn't get
to see a doctor,

15:37.771 --> 15:39.773
we're gonna have
to get you a doctor.

15:39.806 --> 15:42.509
Yeah. Now.

15:42.542 --> 15:45.278
I'm sorry it took you
so long to get in.

15:45.311 --> 15:47.147
It's about time
somebody threatened

15:47.180 --> 15:48.748
to kick that nurse's ass.

15:48.782 --> 15:51.317
Mm, I think we have
to run some tests.

15:51.351 --> 15:53.553
What kind of tests?
Well, first we need

15:53.586 --> 15:56.289
to draw some blood,
little lady. I'll be right back.

15:56.322 --> 15:59.025
Mama, I don't want...
Baby, you have to take the test

15:59.059 --> 16:02.162
in order for you to feel better.
Mom, uh...

16:02.195 --> 16:05.365
I have to tell you something.

16:05.398 --> 16:07.067
What?

16:07.100 --> 16:09.302
I dared Tonya to drink
a hot sauce shake.

16:09.336 --> 16:13.373
A hot sauce shake? Girl, what in
the world would you do that for?

16:13.406 --> 16:14.274
He dared me!

16:17.110 --> 16:19.512
Doctor, I don't think
that'll be necessary.

16:19.546 --> 16:22.649
My son dared her to drink
a hot sauce shake.

16:22.682 --> 16:24.250
A hot sauce shake?

16:24.284 --> 16:28.121
Yeah, you know, vinegar,
hot sauce, syrup and milk.

16:28.154 --> 16:30.190
I didn't know
it'd make her that sick.

16:30.223 --> 16:32.092
I know what to do.

16:34.094 --> 16:36.096
Here.

16:36.129 --> 16:37.697
What is this?
Ipecac.

16:37.731 --> 16:39.599
This is to induce vomiting.

16:39.632 --> 16:41.801
When she's done,
she may have a slight cough.

16:41.835 --> 16:44.504
Give her some Robitussin.

16:44.537 --> 16:47.140
She'll be fine.

16:47.173 --> 16:50.243
<i>Ain't no fussin'</i>
<i>with the 'Tussin.</i>

16:50.276 --> 16:51.277
Ow!

16:54.781 --> 16:59.185
Julius, you gotta take that
truck back over to DeKalb.

16:59.219 --> 17:01.688
I'll do it tomorrow.
No, I need it done now.

17:01.721 --> 17:03.590
You can't find somebody else?

17:03.623 --> 17:06.226
Why should I find somebody else?
I found you.

17:06.259 --> 17:09.129
I want that truck
back over to DeKalb now.

17:09.162 --> 17:12.132
<i>The only person I ever saw</i>
<i>tell my father what to do</i>

17:12.165 --> 17:14.467
<i>was my mother.</i>

17:14.501 --> 17:16.536
You just gonna let him
tell you what to do?

17:16.569 --> 17:20.240
Either that or I won't have
nothing to do. Come on.

17:23.376 --> 17:25.512
Ow.

17:25.545 --> 17:27.080
That hurt.

17:31.151 --> 17:33.520
You worked hard.
Yeah.

17:34.821 --> 17:37.524
Feels kind of good, don't it?
Yeah.

17:37.557 --> 17:39.559
<i>After everything</i>
<i>I'd been through,</i>

17:39.592 --> 17:42.262
<i>I understood my father</i>
<i>a lot more.</i>

17:42.295 --> 17:43.763
<i>Because when you work</i>
<i>that hard,</i>

17:43.797 --> 17:46.166
<i>you think about every dime</i>
<i>you spend.</i>

17:46.199 --> 17:49.402
<i>And I was thinking about how</i>
<i>I was gonna spend mine.</i>

17:50.837 --> 17:53.573
Twenty-five dollars?
That's right.

17:53.606 --> 17:55.275
You earned every penny.

17:55.308 --> 17:57.243
Don't forget
to ice down your arms.

17:57.277 --> 17:58.645
But I need 50 for the jacket.

17:58.678 --> 18:02.682
No, you don't. You want 50.
There's a difference.

18:02.716 --> 18:05.685
When I asked you for the jacket,
you said I should get a job.

18:05.719 --> 18:09.222
And I got a job.
Job didn't pay enough.

18:09.255 --> 18:11.391
Man, you got $25.

18:11.424 --> 18:14.427
I didn't make my first $25
till I was 30 years old.

18:14.461 --> 18:16.429
And I still got two of 'em.

18:16.463 --> 18:19.899
Look, you want the jacket,
save your money.

18:19.933 --> 18:22.569
You can work with me
again next week.

18:22.602 --> 18:24.537
Okay.
Hey...

18:31.244 --> 18:32.846
Bye, Mommy.
See ya.

18:32.879 --> 18:34.614
Have a good day at school.

18:34.647 --> 18:37.550
<i>A few days later, Drew</i>
<i>and Tonya were back in school</i>

18:37.584 --> 18:40.453
<i>and my mother could</i>
<i>go back to her routine.</i>

18:40.487 --> 18:43.356
<i>I've never seen a woman</i>
<i>so happy to clean.</i>

18:43.390 --> 18:44.491
Ooh!

18:49.229 --> 18:52.499
Hello. Hello.

18:56.670 --> 18:58.405
<i>Meanwhile,</i>
<i>I was still wishing</i>

18:58.438 --> 19:00.373
<i>my job had worked out</i>
<i>a little better.</i>

19:00.407 --> 19:02.609
<i>After all I'd gone through</i>
<i>with my father,</i>

19:02.642 --> 19:05.512
<i>I appreciated him</i>
<i>that much more.</i>

19:07.514 --> 19:09.683
Hi, man.
How do you like my jacket?

19:09.716 --> 19:13.186
You got that one?
I got the last one on sale.

19:15.989 --> 19:18.625
<i>But I didn't go out</i>
<i>in the middle of the night</i>

19:18.658 --> 19:20.860
<i>and do all that work</i>
<i>for nothing.</i>

19:20.894 --> 19:23.296
[***]

19:33.306 --> 19:34.908
Aren't you hot in that thing?

19:34.941 --> 19:37.243
Please. I'm fine.

19:38.678 --> 19:39.946
Chris?!

19:39.979 --> 19:44.250
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

19:50.423 --> 19:53.927
[***]

19:53.960 --> 19:56.563
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
